HEADWORD: Mesitylene
<hw>Me*sit"y*lene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless, fragrant liquid, <chform>C6H3(CH3)3</chform>, of the
benzene series of hydrocarbons, obtained by distilling acetone with
sulphuric acid.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Me*sit`y*len"ic</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

